enableForApp.desc: Places all the windows of an app into one place and tab them
enableForApp.doc:
Places all the windows of an app into one place and tab them

Parameters:
 * app - An `hs.application` object or the app title

Returns:
 * None
enableForApp.name: enableForApp
parameters: * app - An `hs.application` object or the app title

focusTab.desc: Focuses a specific tab of an app
focusTab.doc:
Focuses a specific tab of an app

Parameters:
 * app - An `hs.application` object previously enabled for tabbing
 * num - A tab number to switch to

Returns:
 * None

Notes:
 * If num is higher than the number of tabs, the last tab will be focussed
focusTab.name: focusTab
notes: * If num is higher than the number of tabs, the last tab will be focussed
parameters: * app - An `hs.application` object previously enabled for tabbing
* num - A tab number to switch to

tabWindows.desc: Gets a list of the tabs of a window
tabWindows.doc:
Gets a list of the tabs of a window

Parameters:
 * app - An `hs.application` object

Returns:
 * An array of the tabbed windows of an app in the same order as they would be tabbed

Notes:
 * This function can be used when writing tab switchers
tabWindows.name: tabWindows
notes: * This function can be used when writing tab switchers
returns: * An array of the tabbed windows of an app in the same order as they would be tabbed
